en_635755_0	Troops of the 54 Division in Mannar under the Security Force Headquarters - Wanni (SFHQ-W) on account of its 8th anniversary held a number of commemorative programmes during 6 - 9 September.
en_635755_1	Under the supervision of the General Officer Commanding - 54 Division, Brigadier W.G.H.A.S Bandara, religious observances and prayer sessions at Jummah Mosque, Thiruketheeswaram Kovil, Shrine of our Lady of Madu and Mathota Raja Maha Viharaya were given priority.
en_635755_2	A Guard Turn Out and a Guard of Honour to be in accordance with military formalities got underway on the anniversary day at the premises, offering a salute to the General Officer Commanding, 54 Division.
en_635755_3	Later on, an all rank lunch and a grand musical evening in the 54 Division playground took place to coincide with the event.
en_635755_4	An Officers’ get-together at the Officers’ Mess was also a feature in the anniversary programme.
en_635755_5	General Officers Commanding in 56 and 61 Divisions also participated in those events as special guests.
